## ðŸ§© Query Used
```sql
SELECT DISTINCT
    service 
FROM
    services_weekly;

ðŸ“š Key Learnings

SQL (Structured Query Language) is used to interact with relational databases.

SELECT retrieves data from one or more columns in a table.

Limiting columns helps in getting only the relevant information.

Understanding the table structure before querying is beneficial.

ðŸ”‘ Key Notes

LIMIT controls how many records are returned, useful for large datasets.

DESC or DESCRIBE commands help check column details and types.

AS can rename columns temporarily to improve readability.

